The bibliography at the end of the paper
&quot;New directions in cryptography&quot;
has 14 entries, labeled &quot;[1]&quot; through &quot;[14]&quot;.
The numbers &quot;1&quot; through &quot;14&quot;
are examples of bibliography keys.
I&#39;ll abbreviate &quot;bibliography key&quot; as &quot;bibkey&quot; or just &quot;key&quot;.
